descript.abstract: Boundary polygon encompassing all of the lands and waters that WBNERR oversees.
descript.purpose: This layer is created to show a polygon of the Waquoit Bay Boundary where all lands and waters within this polygon are under the protection/observation of WBNERR, if not necessarily owned by. Includes wetland areas that are protected by WBNERR as well as lands that are jointly owned by WBNERR and Massachusetts Department of Fish and Wildlife.
descript.supplinf: Data used for creation (numbered in order of precedence): 1.) Shorelines: used baselayers.mdb\cape_land 2.) Falmouth Parcels: 2006 Falmouth Parcels (Falmouth_06\Fal_basemap.mdb\ParcelCAMA) 2.) Mashpee Parcels: 2004 Mashpee Parcels (Waquoit Bay GIS\Reference Data\Town Data\Mashpee\town_data\parcels_sp83.shp) 3.) Areas encompassing wetlands digitized in using the 2004 Falmouth and Mashpee B/W Imagery - as compared to the old_wbnerr_bound_wet dataset without knowing why some wetlands were included but others were not.

timeperd.current: Boundary of WBNERR's influence current as of November, 2006, as accurate as the time of the data that it is built upon.
